{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"Amended change 733 → patchset 2 (Change-Id Ic2ffd046…, commit dddbeea). Two things:\n\n1. Carries the original SKIP fix (env SKIP: no-commit-to-branch on the pre-commit\n   --all-files step in both test.yml and gerrit-verify.yaml).\n2. ADDS the drift-prevention guard the incident owner asked for:\n   tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py::test_branch_sensitive_precommit_hooks_skipped_in_ci.\n   The existing parity test only compared command *signatures* (both files run the\n   identical `pre-commit run --all-files`), so it was blind to this *context* drift —\n   same command, different git HEAD (main vs detached change ref). The new guard parses\n   .pre-commit-config.yaml for branch-sensitive hooks and fails the build unless each is\n   SKIPped in BOTH workflows' pre-commit step. RED→GREEN proven locally: reverting the\n   SKIP turns the guard RED naming the exact missing skip; restoring it → 4/4 green.\n\nThe push auto-removed the prior LLM-Review-1 (it was an infra veto: coverage-gap /\nllm-unavailable / provider Connection error — NOT a code finding). PS2 re-runs both\nLLM-Review and Verified. Will submit + close once LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1.\n\nSibling sweep: no-commit-to-branch is the only branch-sensitive pre-commit hook, and\nonly test.yml + gerrit-verify.yaml run pre-commit — both fixed; no other siblings.\nDiscovered separately and filed as childsafe-special-springtail (discovered_from this):\na FLAKY test (could not parse HEAD under xdist) — different class, not drift."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784227932495863001,"uuid":"127c8040-a13a-40bf-b123-e2198a389109"}